  "conformsToProfile": "https://uofa.net/vocab#ProfileMinimal",
  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "Credibility evidence package for CFD-based hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) operating conditions. The model predicts absolute hemolysis index (HI) as the quantity of interest for a Class III VAD device. Model Risk Level 5 applies per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 1, driven by the direct patient-safety consequence of hemolysis prediction errors in implantable cardiac assist therapy. All 13 credibility factors have been assessed; seven factors achieved their required gradation levels and six required additional mitigation actions that were subsequently resolved prior to submission. Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation was performed across inlet flow rate, fluid viscosity, and power-law hemolysis model coefficients. The regulatory claim is that the CFD model is sufficiently credible to support a 510(k) substantial equivalence submission for the target VAD device operating between 3 L/min and 6 L/min at 3000–5000 RPM. Decision: Accepted.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-cfd-mrl5-req",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hi-cfd-credibility-claim",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-benchtop-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/monte-carlo-uncertainty-samples-n10000"
  ],
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-velocity-field-piv",
